snippet.textDisplay: That's a pretty standard aircraft gas door. The capacity to be placarded on there is the max USABLE fuel in the tank which is different from the max fuel the tank holds-- this is because the wing's structure is part of the tank so fuel pools up on the spars and is not usable.
